title: Code for v0.0.15
body:
This PR includes the following:

1. PR from @ddnomad to allow access to `HttpData` from `ParsingErrorInfo`. #39 
2. Adding a debug message with the query URL. #40 
3. Making `eventDate` optional. #41 
4. Moving to Rust's own `is_terminal`. #23 
5. Fixing of some lints.
6. Updating of all dependencies of significance.
7. Rework of the bootstrapping code to make it accessible to callers of the client library.
8. Some documentation and re-exports in the client library.

Upgrade to 0.0.14
body:
This PR includes:

1. Changes to clap help colors to match clap v3 help output
2. new rdap-srv-test-data command to generate test data for load testing
3. drill.yaml for using Drill to load test the server
4. change from using pinboard to using arc<tokio::rwlock> to fix memory leak
5. support for RDAP /help queries in rdap-srv and tools.

title: Adding server help to rdap_srv
body: This PR adds RDAP sever /help query support to rdap_srv. It also fixes some formatting issues.

title: removed pinboard in the server
body: This PR removes pinboard in favor of tokio's rwlock. No performance differences can be measured with drill load test, and less memory is used.

title: Minus 5.4 and Bootstrapping in SRV
body:
This PR does two things:
1. Upgrades minus to 5.4 in the CLI which fixes a bug causing an extra line to be emitted.
2. Adds the capability to be a bootstrap server to SRV.

title: issue causing publication problem
body: This poppped up when attempting to publish to crates.io

title: Bug fixes and some small fixes
body:
* `--help` now has information on where the cache is stored.
* fixed autnum bootstrapping bug
* fixed a cache bug that prevented non-Entity object classes from being deserialized from cache
* add `rdap_type` to the `--json-extra` output to help scripts determine the rdap object class
* added common parsing example
* a lot of cleanup and changes to the internal common API
* support for cidr0 extension
* moved from simplelog to tracing-subscriber for the cli
* README updates

* Removes the `--url` flag in favor url query detection.
* Adds insecure connection options
* Fixes bug where bootstrapping was preventing url queries

title: Caching and Bootstrapping
body: This PR delivers on two major features, result caching and bootstrapping.
